					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">Just wanted to note that since all the buttons are latched simultaneously by the shift register, there's virtually no way a normal controller can register conflicting directions. <em>If</em> they weren't all latched simultaneously, the player changing from down to up could theoretically occur between when you read one bit and when you read another, allowing both to read as set.</div>

